#x27;))<br>Sizes | Waists<br>S&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; | 30<br>M&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; | 34<br>t.where(&#x27;Sizes&#x27;, are.contained_in(&#x27;MXL&#x27;))&nbsp; #LOGICAL OR!!!!!<br>Sizes | Waists<br>M&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; | 34<br>L&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; | 38<br>XL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; | 42<br>t.where(&#x27;Sizes&#x27;, are.contained_in(&#x27;L&#x27;))<br>Sizes | Waists<br>L&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; | 38<br>t.where(&#x27;Sizes&#x27;, are.not_contained_in(&#x27;MXL&#x27;)) #LOGICAL OR!!!!!<br>Sizes | Waists<br><br><strong>PDS - the iloc &amp; loc methods&#x2F;For help: &quot;?df.iloc&quot; or &quot;?df.loc&quot;</strong><br>df.iloc[:10]<br>df.iloc[:10, 3:6] #like bds take but can specify columns as well<br>&nbsp;#MUST DO THIS FOR loc<br>df.loc[[&#x27;Apple&#x27;,&#x27;Facebook&#x27;]] #Note the use of double brackets!<br>df.loc[(df[&#x27;market-cap&#x27;] &gt; 70) &amp; (df[&#x27;sector&#x27;] == &#x27;retail&#x27;)]<br><br><strong>BDS to PDS</strong><br>bdf.to_df()<br>bdf.from_df(df-name)<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br></body></html>
